comment_data.body:
we don't need this. if users/plugins want to override `vim.ui.img` we can document how to do it:

```
vim.ui.img = {
  ...
}
```

comment_regular_data.body:
> I'm investigating what it would take to integrate this in a branch of neovide as a means to test. Would such an effort be useful at this time to verify the alternative api?

@Kethku glad you are looking at it! yes, as you noticed this is extremely minimal, to get a basic shape in place and then start getting feedback on it (https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/31399 was going in circles, too much scope for a P0).

We do plan on lifting this into the [UI protocol](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/39434).
